    {
      "id": "reference-view-unification-note-primitive-poles",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Primitive Poles And Hybrid",
      "position": {
        "x": 1577.8333333333335,
        "y": 75
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Primitive Poles And Hybrid\n\nCurrent best model:\n- `PortNode` = minimal reference primitive\n- `DynamicViewNode` = minimal hosted-view primitive\n- `GraphReferenceNode` = hybrid of those two ideas, plus embedded graph runtime\n- `Bridge` = mode on the minimal reference primitive\n\nThis fits the mechanics better than pretending graph reference simply graduates into dynamic view.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
